    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-04-16T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-04-16T17:00:00-05:00" n="780"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d780">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/2117: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-04-16T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 16, 1938—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>127. Your 196, April 8, 3 p.m. The Department approves your proposed action as
                    outlined in the last sentence of your telegram under reference.</p>
                <p>You will of course bear in mind in this connection the Department’s 262 to
                    Nanking, September 24, 1937, 2 p.m.,<note n="20" xml:id="d780fn20">Not
                        printed.</note> and Department’s 14 to Peiping, January 14, 6 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
